What's next?
While checking your security score is just the first of many steps to boosting your password protection, its time to review passwords that could use a little extra attention.
✔
Strengthen your weak passwords
Weak passwords are common, easy-to-guess, or obvious – and make you more susceptible to hackers. Avoid passwords like password1 or asd123. Instead, generate a strong password like S&2x4BsD%9LSk1.



✔
Make your reused passwords unique
The more places you reuse a password, the weaker it becomes – if one site has a security breach, hackers can try the same username and password combination on other sites. Create a unique password for every site login.
